To harness more talented musicians in the country, Saint Square records have launched a commercial recording studio in Lagos. Located in Maryland, Lagos, the studio which was named after the label, was set up in line with the company’s mantra which is to breed life into the entertainment space.   AMVCA 8 announces digital content creator’s day competition     2022 AMVCA: Rema to join Lagbaja for first-ever joint…     Nigerian creatives should bother less about international…   According to the Managing Director, Jason Olakunle, the decision to build a recording studio and throw its door open is a result of the CEO’s plan to revamp and help talented youths yearning for an opportunity to pursue a career in music. “It was a dream by our Chief Executive Officer, Saint Square records, Mr. Square Okusanya, hence the name,Saint Square records. Saint Square has this mind deep within him about how he can revamp the culture of our young people and help them as a lot are talented. He believes in the art as a tool for culture building and a platform for young people to express their gift and has seen how young people make a living from entertainment hence this dream,” Olakunle said.